[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "When it comes to fans of [streetwear](http://www.elle.com.au/fashion/street-style/2016/8/street-wear-street-style-trend/), 'cult following' doesn't even begin to describe them. New collections can sell out in an instant and can rack up eye-watering prices on the resell market. But, when an industry like this attracts the coolest in fashion, it's clear why we all want in on the action."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "***RELATED: ***[THE COOLEST STREETWEAR-INSPIRED LOOKS FOR MAXIMUM CRED](http://www.elle.com.au/fashion/street-style/2016/8/street-wear-street-style-trend/)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "Now, a new rumoured collaboration is set to become the biggest cult buy of 2017, as streetwear giant Supreme may be joining forces with Louis Vuitton. 'Hypebeasts' everywhere are having a mini meltdown across social media after a model at a Louis Vuitton casting spotted a white sweater featuring LV's embossed monogram print and the Supreme box logo."
  },
  {
    "type": "image",
    "label": "Image",
    "content": {
      "url": "http://d3lp4xedbqa8a5.cloudfront.net/s3/digital-cougar-assets/Elle/2017/01/06/108629/louis-supreme-1.png",
      "title": "",
      "caption": "",
      "link": "https://www.instagram.com/p/BOz1vcgB15B/",
      "valid": true
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "This isn't the only clue. Vuitton's head of menswear, Kim Jones, also posted (and then deleted) an image of the Supreme emoji sticker plastered on a monogram Vuitton product. He even recently appeared at the opening of the brand's first Paris store."
  },
  {
    "type": "image",
    "label": "Image",
    "content": {
      "url": "http://d3lp4xedbqa8a5.cloudfront.net/s3/digital-cougar-assets/Elle/2017/01/06/108629/C1RNGYHXEAIljD2-(1).jpg",
      "title": "",
      "caption": "",
      "link": "https://twitter.com/TheSupremeSaint/status/816362718466867200",
      "valid": true
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "While it's no surprise that these two fashion leaders could join forces, relations between the pair haven't always been friendly. Back in 2000, Supreme plastered Louis Vuitton's monogram print all over their skate decks which resulted in a hefty copyright lawsuit. Two weeks later, the streetwear giant recalled the product, thus making it one of the most covetable items in the brand's history."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "Fast forward to today, and Supreme has grounded its position as the tour de force of streetwear. Jones has also been more open to new urban collections with LV, pursuing a much-hyped collab with Nike and Japanese streetwear brand fragment design. In other words, the two are pretty much a perfect fit."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "***RELATED: ***[YOUR INSTA-FEED WILL BE DOMINATED BY NIKE'S NEW ROSE GOLD SNEAKERS](http://www.elle.com.au/news/fashion-news/2016/11/where-to-buy-nike-rose-gold-sneakers-australia/)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "If this dream collaboration does come true, one thing is for certain: the resell prices on these hyped items are not going to be cheap, but you're going to want every single piece either way."
  }
]
